---

<div class="govuk-width-container">
  <%= partial "shared/get-help/breadcrumbs", locals: { page: "Connect with a Mac" } %>
  <div class="govuk-main-wrapper">
    <div class="govuk-grid-row">
      <div class="govuk-grid-column-one-third">
          <%= partial 'shared/get-help/sidebar' %>
      </div>
      <main class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds" role="main" id="main">
        <h1 class="govuk-heading-l">Connect to GovWifi with a Mac</h1>
        <p class="govuk-body">
          Your device should connect automatically when you select <strong>GovWifi</strong> from your list of available wifi networks and enter your GovWifi password.
        </p>
        <p class="govuk-body">
          If your device doesn't connect automatically:
        </p>
        <ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Select the wifi icon at the top right of your screen.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Select <strong>GovWifi</strong>.</p>
            <img src="https://www.wifi.service.gov.uk/images/troubleshooting/mac-os-step-2.jpg" class="img-fluid" alt="Screenshot of WiFi credentials prompt on macOS">
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Enter the username and password you received by email or text.</p>
            <p class="govuk-inset-text">Your password is case sensitive. It's 3 words without spaces. The first letter of each word is capitalised.</p></li>
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Select <strong>Join</strong>. You will be asked to confirm the network is genuine by checking the certificate.</p>
            <img src="https://www.wifi.service.gov.uk/images/troubleshooting/mac-os-step-4.jpg" class="img-fluid" alt="Screenshot of Verify Certificate dialog on macOS">
          </li>
          <li>
            <p class="govuk-body">Select <strong>Show Certificate.</strong></p>
            <div class="govuk-warning-text">
              <span class="govuk-warning-text__icon" aria-hidden="true">!</span>
              <strong class="govuk-warning-text__text">
                <span class="govuk-warning-text__assistive">Warning</span>
                Check that the certificate is called wifi.service.gov.uk and it's issued by GeoTrust RSA CA 2018.
              </strong>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>Select <strong>Continue</strong>.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>Your device will ask you for your computer password to save these settings.</p>
            <p class="govuk-inset-text">This is the password you normally use to sign into your computer.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
        <p class="govuk-body">
          You should now be connected to Govwifi.
        </p>
        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Support</h2>
        <p class="govuk-body">
          If you still have problems connecting to GovWifi, contact the IT support desk for the building you're in.
        </p>
      </main>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
